      "One proposal we have for this is having an r.args term which would be akin\r\nto pythons *.\r\nOn Jul 4, 2013 12:48 PM, \"Daniel Mewes\" <notifications@github.com> wrote:\r\n\r\n> That's actually the reason for why I have decided to use array parameters\r\n> instead of variadic functions in PHP-RQL.\r\n> Having to write\r\n> getAll([1, 2, 3])\r\n> is not much worse than\r\n> getAll(1, 2, 3)\r\n> in my opinion.\r\n> I actually even think that the first variant is better, because it\r\n> explicitly shows the structure of the arguments. This is an advantage as\r\n> soon as something like the additional index parameter comes into play.\r\n>\r\n> Of course the JS, Python and Ruby APIs do already use variadic functions,\r\n> so I don't think that it should be changed at this point.\r\n>\r\n> One option I could think of would be to support an \"args\" field in the\r\n> optargs map.\r\n> So you could write something like\r\n>\r\n> var arrayId = [1,2,3];\r\n> r.table(\"test\").getAll( {args: arrayId} ).run(...)\r\n>\r\n> It is not very pretty, but might still be useful for some users.\r\n>\r\n> \8212\r\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub<https://github.com/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/1127#issuecomment-20491531>\r\n> .\r\n>"
